h_1 = AK \cdot \sin w \quad \quad \text { and } \quad \quad {h_2 = KC \cdot \sin w}
ad + bc = 2R \sin w (AK + KC) = 2R \cdot AC \sin w
ab + cd = 2R \cdot BD \sin (\pi - w)
\sin w = \sin (\pi - w)
\frac{ad + bc}{ab + cd} = \frac{2R \cdot AC \sin w}{2R \cdot BD \sin (\pi - w)} = \frac{AC}{BD}
